### Phase 2 — n8n Inbound Webhook (Static JSON)
- Created a new n8n workflow called "Retell inbound"
- Added a **Webhook** node: Method POST, Path `retell-inbound`, Response = "Using Respond to Webhook node"
- Added a **Respond to Webhook** node connected after Webhook
- Set response body to static JSON (hardcoded test values):
```
{
  "call_inbound": {
    "dynamic_variables": {
      "airline": "Demo Air",
      "confirmation_number": "ABC123",
      "last_name_expected": "Test"
    }
  }
}
```
- Activated workflow and copied Production URL
- Pasted Production URL into Retell → Phone Number → Inbound webhook
- Also set Inbound call agent on the number (important — was missing initially)
- Tested with PowerShell POST to confirm JSON response returned correctly
- Tested with real phone call — agent said "Demo Air" and "ABC123" correctly

**PowerShell test command:**
```
Invoke-WebRequest -Method Post -Uri "https://sri3.app.n8n.cloud/webhook-test/retell-inbound" -ContentType "application/json" -Body '{"hello":"test"}'
```

**Key lessons learned:**
- Use Production URL (not webhook-test) for Retell
- Workflow must be Active in n8n
- Inbound call agent must be set on the phone number in Retell
- fx (expression mode) must be OFF for plain JSON, ON for expressions
- "Execute this step" only works when previous nodes have run — use "Execute workflow" instead
- Test URL = for PowerShell testing; Production URL = for real Retell calls
- Webhook node output = what came IN; Respond to Webhook = what goes OUT

