### Phase 3 — Google Sheets Integration
- Created Google Sheet named "AI Online Travel Agent Proactive Use..."
- Sheet tab: "Passenger list"
- Column headers (exact spelling matters):
  - phone, airline, confirmation, last_name_expected, has_connection, connecting_airline, connecting_confirmation, connection_city, connection_update
- Added one test row with phone number matching caller ID
- Set up Google Sheets OAuth2 credential in n8n (same Google account as sheet owner)
- Shared sheet with "Anyone with the link can view"
- Added **Google Sheets** node (Get Row(s)) between Webhook and Respond to Webhook
  - Node name in n8n: "Get row(s) in sheet"
  - Credential: Google Sheets account
  - Resource: Sheet Within Document
  - Operation: Get Row(s)
  - Document: AI Online Travel Agent sheet
  - Sheet: Passenger list
  - No filter yet (reads all rows)
- Updated Respond to Webhook to use expressions (fx ON) pulling from Google Sheets:

```
{
  "call_inbound": {
    "dynamic_variables": {
      "airline": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.airline }}",
      "confirmation_number": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.confirmation }}",
      "last_name_expected": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.last_name_expected }}",
      "has_connection": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.has_connection }}",
      "connecting_airline": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.connecting_airline }}",
      "connecting_confirmation": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.connecting_confirmation }}",
      "connection_city": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.connection_city }}",
      "connection_update": "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.connection_update }}"
    }
  }
}
```

**Key lesson:** Expression node references use the exact node name in quotes: `$('Get row(s) in sheet')`. If the name is wrong, you get "Referenced node doesn't exist" error.

