## Phase 7 — Weather Tool (completed)
- Created new n8n workflow "Weather Tool"
- Webhook node: POST, path `weather-tool`
- Get Coordinates node: HTTP Request GET to Nominatim (OpenStreetMap)
  - URL: https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/search
  - Parameters: q = city from args, format = json, limit = 1
  - Header: User-Agent: TravelVoiceAgent/1.0
  - NOTE: Open-Meteo geocoding API blocked on n8n Cloud — use Nominatim instead
- Get Weather node: HTTP Request GET to Open-Meteo
  - URL: https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast
  - Parameters: latitude/longitude from Get Coordinates, current_weather=true, temperature_unit=fahrenheit, wind_speed_unit=mph, timezone=America/New_York
  - Drag and drop lat/lon from left pane — do not type expressions manually
- Respond to Webhook: returns weather_summary sentence with city, temperature, wind speed
- Added get_weather Custom Function in Retell agent
  - URL: Production webhook URL of Weather Tool workflow
  - Parameters JSON schema: city (string, required)
- Added Get Weather node to Retell Conversation Flow canvas
  - Transition from Welcome Node: "User asks about weather"
  - Transitions from Get Weather: "After weather is provided" and "Else" both back to Welcome Node
  - Prompt inside Get Weather node: tell caller city, temperature, wind speed in one short sentence
- Tested with real call — tool invoked correctly, returned real live weather (74.6F, 8.5 mph)

Key lessons learned:
- Always use drag and drop from left pane in n8n instead of typing expressions
- Use Simulation in Retell to test without making real calls
- Retell sends tool args under body.args.city in production calls
- Get Weather node needs a prompt/instructions field to tell agent what to say
- Conversation Flow nodes need transitions connected or Retell throws loop error

