## Bugs & Lessons Learned — Full Summary

### Day 1 — Retell + n8n Inbound Setup

**Webhook & Response Issues**
- Bug: "No Respond to Webhook node found" error. Cause: Webhook node was added without a Respond to Webhook node. Fix: always pair Webhook with Respond to Webhook.
- Bug: Response body empty (RawContentLength 0). Cause: fx expression mode was ON but empty. Fix: turn fx OFF for plain JSON, ON only for expressions.
- Bug: Wrong URL given to Retell. Cause: Test URL (webhook-test) used instead of Production URL. Fix: always activate workflow and use Production URL for Retell.

**Retell Configuration Issues**
- Bug: Agent said literal {{airline}} instead of real value. Cause: Inbound call agent was set to None on the phone number. Fix: always assign an agent to the phone number in Retell settings.
- Bug: Dynamic variables never loaded. Cause: workflow was not Active. Fix: toggle workflow Active before real calls.
- Bug: Variables still not showing. Cause: Retell was hitting Test URL not Production. Fix: paste Production URL into Retell phone number inbound webhook setting.

**Google Sheets Lookup Issues**
- Bug: Sheet node spinning forever. Cause: "Execute this step" used instead of "Execute workflow." Fix: always use Execute workflow so previous nodes pass data through.
- Bug: Filter returning no data. Cause: phone number in sheet had no plus sign but Retell sends +17037312723. Fix: strip plus sign using .replace('+', '') in the filter expression.
- Bug: Filter still not working. Cause: phone stored as number type in Google Sheets. Fix: format phone column as Plain Text, then use .toString() in the expression.
- Bug: "Referenced node doesn't exist" error. Cause: node name in expression didn't match actual node name. Fix: always copy exact node name from top of node panel.

