### Day 2 — Weather Tool

**n8n Expression Issues**
- Bug: URL turned red with & in it. Cause: & is a special character that breaks n8n expression mode. Fix: use Query Parameters section instead of putting parameters in the URL.
- Bug: Coordinates undefined. Cause: expression path wrong between test and production payloads. Fix: use drag and drop from left pane instead of typing expressions manually.
- Bug: City name undefined. Cause: Retell wraps tool arguments under body.args.city in production but test payloads use body.city. Fix: always check Webhook node output in the actual failing execution.

**API Issues**
- Bug: Open-Meteo geocoding 403 Forbidden. Cause: n8n Cloud server IP blocked by that API. Fix: switched to Nominatim (OpenStreetMap) with User-Agent header.
- Bug: Nominatim response format different from Open-Meteo. Cause: old expressions used results[0].latitude but Nominatim uses [0].lat and [0].lon. Fix: drag and drop after a successful run to auto-generate correct path.

**Retell Canvas Issues**
- Bug: Loop error ending call early. Cause: Get Weather node had no transitions connected. Fix: connect "After weather is provided" and "Else" back to Welcome Node.
- Bug: Agent said nothing useful after weather data returned. Cause: Get Weather node had no prompt. Fix: add instructions inside node telling agent to relay city, temperature, wind speed.
- Bug: City name blank in weather response. Cause: display_name expression not matching Nominatim format. Fix: use $('Get Coordinates').item.json[0].name.

---

### Cross-Cutting Lessons (apply everywhere)
- Always drag and drop in n8n — never type expressions manually
- Always check the actual failing execution Webhook node to find real payload structure
- Test URL = PowerShell testing only; Production URL = Retell always
- Use Retell Simulation before making real calls to save time
- Every Retell Conversation Flow node needs both a prompt AND transitions connected
- Execute workflow not Execute step — step only works when previous nodes already ran
- Node names in expressions must match exactly — copy from top of node panel
